ROLE: You are a principal designer/engineer. Your task is to transform https://remmanidev.com into a best-in-class, HR-ready portfolio.

GOALS
- Make HR understand my value in <5 seconds.
- Modern, premium SaaS look. Flawless responsiveness, A11y, and performance.
- Clear hiring funnels: Download resume, book call, email me.

TECH
- Html, css, javascript
- Content as MDX for projects/blog. Add simple config JSON for hero and links.

SITEMAP
- / (Home): Hero, proof points, 3–6 project highlights, services, tech stack, testimonials, CTA.
- /projects: Grid + filters; each → case study page (/projects/[slug]).
- /about: Short story, experience timeline, certs, photo.
- /resume: Render 1-page resume + “Download PDF” server action.
- /blog: MDX posts.
- /contact: Email form + direct links; also a persistent contact dock.

COMPONENTS
- Navbar (sticky, blur, active section highlights), Footer.
- Section wrapper (max-width, rhythm), Grid system (12-col), Card primitives.
- ProjectCard (logo/cover, tags, 2-line summary, metric).
- CaseStudy template: Context → Constraints → Architecture → Before/After → Metrics → Learnings → Stack.
- TestimonialCard with avatar, role, quote.
- CTA Banner with dual buttons (primary resume, secondary call).
- Sticky contact dock (copy email, LinkedIn, GitHub, Calendly).

DESIGN SYSTEM
- Tokens: colors, spacing, radii (rounded-2xl), shadows (soft), typography scale.
- Palette: ink #0B1220 / slate neutrals / teal accent; balanced for light/dark.
- Motion: subtle entrance on scroll, hover lift, focus rings. 200–300ms ease-out.
- Empty states, 404, cookie-light “no tracking” notice, skeleton loaders.

COPY (HR-FIRST)
- Hero: “Yassine REMMANI — Full-Stack Engineer (Spring Boot • Next.js • PostgreSQL • Docker). I build resilient multi-tenant platforms and high-impact SaaS.” 
- Proof points: “4,000+ dealer sites”, “Realtime inventory sync”, “0→1 platform”, “-40% TTFB”.
- Buttons: Primary “Download 1-page Resume (PDF)”, Secondary “Book 15-min call”.
- Project metrics: concrete numbers, latency, adoption, cost savings.

PERFORMANCE/SEO/A11y
- Lighthouse ≥95. Optimize images, prefetch routes, dynamic OG images, sitemap, robots.
- Schema.org Person + Project + BlogPosting. Canonicals, OpenGraph, Twitter cards.
- WCAG AA: roles/landmarks, labels, skip links, keyboard tab order, color contrast.

INTEGRATIONS
- Add /api/og for social banners.
- Optional: Calendly link; simple email copy button.
- Analytics: lightweight (Plausible) with explicit toggle.

DELIVERABLES
- Implement full UI with placeholder content from current site.
- One best-in-class case study fully written and styled as reference.
- Resume generator route: /resume -> PDF (server action) + print styles.
- README: how to add projects/posts, change theme, deploy.

WORKFLOW
1) Audit current site → produce a markdown plan: final sitemap, component list, and a task checklist.
2) Implement design system + layout shell, then pages, then polish (motion, a11y).
3) Replace hero with HR-focused copy + CTAs.
4) Add flagship case study and resume page.
5) Run performance and accessibility pass; fix regressions.
6) Provide me with a summary of changes and next steps.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Above-the-fold communicates role + value + proof points + CTAs on mobile/desktop.
- Visual consistency (tokens), dark/light perfect parity.
- At least 95 Lighthouse on mobile and desktop in CI preview.
- No a11y violations on axe DevTools basic scan.
